    <system:String x:Key="ChatSession.Instruction.1">1. This setting is written immediately to PresentationUI.xml in the current configuration directory.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="ChatSession.Instruction.2">2. It controls whether new collapsible reasoning blocks enter the UI expanded or collapsed.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="ChatSession.Instruction.3">3. Manual expand/collapse state in the current chat view is not forcibly reset during streaming refresh.</system:String>

    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.Page.Description">Configure whether the Lateral File System is enabled and which working root is shared by virtualization roots.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.Page.Hint">Frontend changes are written to XML automatically. LateralFileSystemTree.xml is created only after the first virtual folder is created.</system:String>
