    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.Enabled.Label">Enable Lateral File System</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.Enabled.Content">Allow creating, maintaining, and activating Lateral File System virtualization roots.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.WorkingRoot.Label">Working Root Directory</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.WorkingRoot.Hint.HasValue">All Lateral File System virtualization roots will be created under this directory.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.WorkingRoot.Hint.Empty">Choose a working root directory.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.Section.Environment">Environment Status</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.Backend.Label">Virtualization Backend</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.Section.Constraints">Constraints</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.Instruction.1">1. All virtualization roots must live under the working root directory.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.Instruction.2">2. LateralFileSystemTree.xml is not created during configuration; the backend creates it after the first Lateral File System node is created.</system:String>
    <system:String x:Key="LateralFileSystem.Instruction.3">3. Enabled state and working root changes on this page are written to the configuration file immediately.</system:String>
